<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01058d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01058d">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01058d"> 58(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bought a donkey for / &frac12; a crown</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Donkey For Half A Crown</mark>.&mdash;John Glynn, Galway, was sent to prison for a month for buying a donkey for half a crown from a schoolboy who had found the animal wandering. R.J. Hughes, a local shopkeeper, was also sentenced to a month&apos;s imprisonment for receiving stolen tobacco from four boys whose ages ranged from eight to ten. The tobacco had been stolen from a trawler bound for Connemara. <small> <a name="IT30nov22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT30nov22"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (30 November 1922) 7/8</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05128i" href="c05all.htm#c05128i">VI.C.05:128(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
